799
01:09:23,739 --> 01:09:25,673
Danny!

800
01:09:28,478 --> 01:09:31,072
Danny, please.

801
01:09:31,247 --> 01:09:32,680
- Please don't do this.
- Get away from me!

802
01:09:32,849 --> 01:09:33,975
Danny, listen to me.

803
01:09:34,150 --> 01:09:35,174
It's all a lie!

804
01:09:35,284 --> 01:09:37,115
I don't want to hear anymore
of your lies!

805
01:09:38,621 --> 01:09:40,851
Danny, what you heard is not
the truth. It's not what I want.

806
01:09:41,023 --> 01:09:43,890
What do you want?
You don't want me!

807
01:09:44,527 --> 01:09:45,892
You never wanted me!

808
01:09:46,062 --> 01:09:48,326
- You only wanted a piece of me!
- I want my son.

809
01:09:48,498 --> 01:09:50,056
Another lie!

810
01:09:51,400 --> 01:09:55,063
It's true, Danny. I'm sick.
But that doesn't matter anymore.

811
01:09:55,171 --> 01:09:55,933
[Yells]

812
01:09:56,038 --> 01:09:57,528
Please, Danny.

813
01:09:57,640 --> 01:09:59,801
Everything about you is a lie.

814
01:10:01,544 --> 01:10:03,535
That's almost the truth.

815
01:10:03,646 --> 01:10:07,377
Danny, I came back here
for all the wrong reasons.

816
01:10:07,783 --> 01:10:09,978
Something inside me has changed.

817
01:10:10,152 --> 01:10:12,086
I see how things
could have been between us.

818
01:10:12,255 --> 01:10:13,153
I see what we've become.

819
01:10:14,257 --> 01:10:15,383
Danny!

820
01:10:16,259 --> 01:10:18,022
Nearly hit the jackpot there,
didn't you?

821
01:10:18,194 --> 01:10:19,821
Let's try it again, huh?

822
01:10:19,996 --> 01:10:21,054
Danny, no!

823
01:10:23,666 --> 01:10:24,826
- Let me go!
- No.

824
01:10:24,934 --> 01:10:26,094
Let me go! Let me go!

825
01:10:26,202 --> 01:10:27,430
No!

826
01:10:27,870 --> 01:10:29,929
[Danny cries]

827
01:10:35,745 --> 01:10:38,305
Why did you do this to me?!

828
01:10:38,414 --> 01:10:41,383
Why did you take
everything away? Why?

829
01:10:42,251 --> 01:10:44,481
Why did you leave me?

830
01:10:47,223 --> 01:10:49,987
I was just a little boy.

831
01:10:50,826 --> 01:10:53,693
A little boy.

832
01:10:55,531 --> 01:10:57,999
What was wrong with me?

833
01:10:58,100 --> 01:11:01,763
What was wrong with me?

834
01:11:01,871 --> 01:11:04,669
There was nothing wrong
with you, Danny.

835
01:11:05,241 --> 01:11:07,106
Something was wrong with <i>me.</i>

836
01:11:07,209 --> 01:11:09,439
[Sobs]

837
01:11:09,545 --> 01:11:13,311
I'm sorry for not being there for you
all these years.

838
01:11:14,116 --> 01:11:16,778
I'm sorry for all the times we missed.

839
01:11:17,853 --> 01:11:21,414
But most of all, I'm sorry
for not being your father.

840
01:11:22,925 --> 01:11:27,259
Danny, you got to forgive me,
because I can't forgive myself.

841
01:11:41,043 --> 01:11:42,840
I'm sorry.

842
01:11:45,081 --> 01:11:46,742
I'm sorry.

843
01:12:02,598 --> 01:12:04,862
[Danny sobs]

844
01:12:58,354 --> 01:13:00,151
Can we talk?

845
01:13:14,336 --> 01:13:16,668
The place hasn't changed much.

846
01:13:20,910 --> 01:13:23,879
But I've learned some lessons, Danny.

847
01:13:24,246 --> 01:13:26,680
Some important things.

848
01:13:28,517 --> 01:13:31,145
You don't like vegetarian pizza.

849
01:13:34,724 --> 01:13:36,817
I made some mistakes.

850
01:13:41,330 --> 01:13:43,560
I made a lot of mistakes.

851
01:13:47,269 --> 01:13:48,668
DANNY:
What was he like?

852
01:13:48,771 --> 01:13:49,999
Your grandfather?

853
01:13:50,773 --> 01:13:53,435
He was tough but fair.

854
01:13:53,609 --> 01:13:57,170
Oh, he was a hell
of a fisherman, though.

855
01:13:58,414 --> 01:14:00,439
I remember this one time.

856
01:14:00,549 --> 01:14:02,642
It was near the end
of this competition.

857
01:14:02,752 --> 01:14:04,276
I nearly held the big one,

858
01:14:04,386 --> 01:14:07,082
and then the horn sounded,
ending the contest.

859
01:14:07,189 --> 01:14:08,656
He was the winner for sure,

860
01:14:08,758 --> 01:14:12,819
but Dad, he congratulated me
on the catch.

861
01:14:13,262 --> 01:14:15,856
And then he made me
throw it back in.

862
01:14:15,965 --> 01:14:18,866
He always played by the rules.

863
01:14:18,968 --> 01:14:24,133
As time went by,
I got tired of playing by his rules.

864
01:14:25,574 --> 01:14:28,907
We shared some great times
out at that lake, though.

865
01:14:29,979 --> 01:14:33,142
Sometimes we just
cast out our lines,

866
01:14:33,249 --> 01:14:36,548
sit back, look at the water.

867
01:14:37,520 --> 01:14:40,353
We didn't even care
if it rained a little.

868
01:14:43,325 --> 01:14:48,456
Dad had this kind
of quiet strength about him.

869
01:14:50,800 --> 01:14:53,200
I see a lot of him in you.

870
01:14:56,138 --> 01:14:58,663
You were named after him, Danny.

871
01:15:01,143 --> 01:15:02,576
I know.

872
01:15:10,252 --> 01:15:12,015
SKIP: You hungry?
You want something to eat?

873
01:15:12,121 --> 01:15:15,113
DANNY: I don't know.
What time is it?

874
01:15:16,392 --> 01:15:17,791
SKIP:
I don't know.

875
01:15:17,893 --> 01:15:20,453
I can't find my watch.

876
01:15:31,140 --> 01:15:33,506
Tell me about you and my mom.

877
01:15:34,510 --> 01:15:35,772
Your mother.

878
01:15:37,580 --> 01:15:40,413
Your mother was the love of my life.

879
01:15:41,183 --> 01:15:44,949
She loved you, Danny,
from the moment you were born.

880
01:15:46,322 --> 01:15:49,951
She was this actress
auditioning in Los Angeles.

881
01:15:50,059 --> 01:15:53,654
I was pushing sets around
for six bucks an hour.

882
01:15:54,196 --> 01:15:55,857
We met.

883
01:15:57,132 --> 01:15:59,066
We fell in love.

884
01:16:00,603 --> 01:16:02,901
We never had much.

885
01:16:04,974 --> 01:16:07,738
But we had you.

886
01:16:08,244 --> 01:16:12,772
One day she was auditioning
for some soap opera or something.

887
01:16:12,882 --> 01:16:15,146
She was running late.

888
01:16:15,551 --> 01:16:17,542
And this truck...

889
01:16:18,087 --> 01:16:20,453
...crossed the divider line.

890
01:16:27,162 --> 01:16:29,790
It took me a long time to get over it.

891
01:16:32,368 --> 01:16:34,632
Maybe I never have.

892
01:16:38,574 --> 01:16:39,836
Carrie...

893
01:16:40,609 --> 01:16:42,770
She helped me raise you.

894
01:16:44,179 --> 01:16:46,477
And after a while, I couldn't
deal with it anymore, Danny.

895
01:16:46,582 --> 01:16:50,143
I just got up, and I...
and I left.

896
01:16:52,321 --> 01:16:54,482
She loves you, Danny.

897
01:16:55,391 --> 01:16:58,622
She loves you just like
you were her own son.

898
01:16:58,727 --> 01:16:59,694
I know.

899
01:17:11,740 --> 01:17:13,799
I'll do it, Dad.

900
01:17:16,145 --> 01:17:17,942
Whatever it is.

901
01:17:20,249 --> 01:17:22,012
Danny.

902
01:17:23,152 --> 01:17:25,416
Danny, I'm all right.

903
01:17:33,062 --> 01:17:38,056
Mom, something's really wrong
with... with Dad... Skip.

904
01:17:45,040 --> 01:17:46,564
Mom.

905
01:17:46,675 --> 01:17:48,506
- Hey.
- Let me take your bag.

906
01:17:50,279 --> 01:17:53,680
Um, are you hungry?
I just threw some bacon and eggs in.

907
01:17:53,782 --> 01:17:56,546
Danny, are you feeling okay?

908
01:17:57,886 --> 01:17:59,854
I'm worried about Dad.

909
01:17:59,955 --> 01:18:02,355
He takes these pills.

910
01:18:16,538 --> 01:18:19,268
This is a very serious prescription.

911
01:18:21,877 --> 01:18:23,174
This is for people who...

912
01:18:23,345 --> 01:18:24,778
That's right.

913
01:18:29,351 --> 01:18:30,409
It's okay.

914
01:18:34,156 --> 01:18:36,249
It's not okay.

915
01:18:37,059 --> 01:18:39,892
Is that why you came back here?
So you could die on him?

916
01:18:50,506 --> 01:18:54,875
You came home for a partial
from Danny, didn't you?

917
01:18:55,511 --> 01:18:57,069
- You have no right!
- Carrie.

918
01:18:57,179 --> 01:19:00,478
- You have no right to ask that of him!
- Carrie.

919
01:19:01,984 --> 01:19:03,611
You're right.

920
01:19:04,720 --> 01:19:07,018
You've always been right.

921
01:19:10,926 --> 01:19:13,326
I got so much more than I came for.

922
01:19:13,429 --> 01:19:18,059
I got my son back,
and I got my sister back.

923
01:19:20,202 --> 01:19:23,535
Those are the most
important things in life.

924
01:19:25,607 --> 01:19:28,405
Maybe one day he'll believe me.

925
01:19:29,745 --> 01:19:30,575
And you.

926
01:19:34,149 --> 01:19:36,640
This is gonna hurt him.

927
01:19:39,721 --> 01:19:42,246
This is gonna hurt me.

928
01:19:42,624 --> 01:19:44,717
I'm so sorry for those things
I said to you.

929
01:19:44,893 --> 01:19:46,554
Don't, don't.

930
01:19:46,662 --> 01:19:47,560
Don't, don't.

931
01:19:52,568 --> 01:19:54,695
Did they say how long?

932
01:19:58,040 --> 01:19:59,667
Elliot.

933
01:20:00,175 --> 01:20:01,665
Skip.

934
01:20:02,211 --> 01:20:03,678
Yeah.

935
01:20:04,279 --> 01:20:07,146
I want everything in a trust.

936
01:20:07,649 --> 01:20:10,083
Yeah monthly...
monthly income.

937
01:20:14,590 --> 01:20:16,057
DANNY:
Oh!

938
01:20:17,092 --> 01:20:18,286
Oh, don't fall!

939
01:20:18,393 --> 01:20:19,724
I wish Dad could see this.

940
01:20:32,774 --> 01:20:35,265
How's that doctor friend of yours?

941
01:20:35,377 --> 01:20:37,004
He's good.

942
01:20:37,579 --> 01:20:38,637
We're good.

943
01:20:39,681 --> 01:20:40,670
That's good.

944
01:20:44,119 --> 01:20:48,988
I want you to give my attorney,
Elliot, a call when...

945
01:20:50,526 --> 01:20:52,653
...when you get around to it.

946
01:21:00,035 --> 01:21:01,024
How are you feeling?

947
01:21:02,204 --> 01:21:04,502
Like I'm about 100 years old.

948
01:21:07,276 --> 01:21:10,040
They say it's supposed to rain.

949
01:21:14,449 --> 01:21:16,349
Maybe tomorrow, huh?

950
01:21:17,319 --> 01:21:18,877
Maybe.

951
01:22:19,448 --> 01:22:23,214
You know, you're...
you're really warm.

952
01:22:30,325 --> 01:22:33,761
I thought that we
would go to the lake.

953
01:22:35,397 --> 01:22:37,627
You said we should go sometime.

954
01:22:38,634 --> 01:22:39,999
I did.

955
01:22:40,335 --> 01:22:41,768
Honey, I don't think it's a good idea.

956
01:22:54,283 --> 01:22:55,875
You drive.

957
01:22:57,219 --> 01:22:59,050
I'm not allowed.

958
01:23:00,489 --> 01:23:02,320
Neither am I.

959
01:23:15,837 --> 01:23:18,032
It's a beautiful day.

960
01:23:21,376 --> 01:23:22,775
It is.

961
01:23:27,049 --> 01:23:29,449
So, what do you want to do
with the rest of your life?

962
01:23:31,853 --> 01:23:33,377
I don't know.

963
01:23:35,557 --> 01:23:36,751
I like to draw.

964
01:23:38,226 --> 01:23:39,318
You're an artist.

965
01:23:40,395 --> 01:23:42,829
- A good one.
- No, I'm not.

966
01:23:44,466 --> 01:23:47,492
Danny, there's gonna be
so many people in your life

967
01:23:47,602 --> 01:23:49,763
putting you down.

968
01:23:49,871 --> 01:23:52,601
You don't need any help from you.

969
01:23:52,708 --> 01:23:54,539
You understand?

970
01:23:56,745 --> 01:23:57,473
Yeah.

971
01:24:00,415 --> 01:24:05,512
You got a lot of opportunities
to do some great things.

972
01:24:09,024 --> 01:24:11,686
I want you to take advantage of them.

973
01:24:23,772 --> 01:24:25,831
My father...

974
01:24:27,242 --> 01:24:31,201
He taught me how to be a good man,
Danny, and I wasn't.

975
01:24:35,917 --> 01:24:38,351
Be a good man, Danny.

976
01:24:40,856 --> 01:24:42,790
Be happy.

977
01:24:44,726 --> 01:24:46,660
Honest.

978
01:24:51,500 --> 01:24:52,990
Good.

979
01:25:00,509 --> 01:25:02,977
We should have come here
a long time ago.

980
01:25:29,438 --> 01:25:31,269
Dad.

981
01:25:37,579 --> 01:25:38,409
Dad.

982
01:25:46,688 --> 01:25:48,246
Dad.

983
